ence is a raceme, 5-8 cm long, bearing 2-5 flowers, which are yellowish-green, 1.5-2 cm long, and have a lip with a short spur. The sepals and petals are similar in shape and size, and the labellum is triangular and has a distinctive spur. It is a rare and endemic variety found in the Sierra de Guadarrama mountains in Spain."}